{"author":{"id":"18b4819b9e909d2858249446d2d0b2583f4f76577f1d616ac7f71b60bdeb6c9e"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1692267870,"nonce":"2/Q2XaazCV0rIcJF26kXgm48XWs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5ujMCW","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5444","origin":"github"},"title":"Unused parameters in Scmap tools","message":"Some scmap tools in Galaxy have parameters which don't seem to be utilised. Additionally there are some parameters which could be included which can help get the best results from the tools.\n\n### Select features\n\n```Scmap select features``` includes the parameter **Number of features** which looking in scmap-cli ([here](https://github.com/ebi-gene-expression-group/scmap-cli/blob/develop/scmap-select-features.R#L21)) isn't being used in any of the code.\n\nFrom the scmap [documentation](https://rdrr.io/bioc/scmap/man/selectFeatures.html) the parameter ```n_features``` should be used in the following way:\n```R\nselectFeatures(\n    object, \n    n_features=500, \n    suppress_plot=FALSE\n)\n```\n\n\n### Cluster projection\n\n```Scmap cluster projection``` includes the parameter **threshold** which also seems to not be utilised in the scmap-cli tool [here](https://github.com/ebi-gene-expression-group/scmap-cli/blob/develop/scmap-scmap-cluster.R#L28)\n\nLooking at the scmap [documentation](https://rdrr.io/bioc/scmap/man/scmapCluster.html) for that function the ```threshold``` parameter is used in the following way:\n```R\nscmapCluster(\n    projection, \n    index_list, \n    threshold=0.7\n)\n```\n\n### Cell projection\n\nThe ```Scmap cell projection``` tool could also include two additional parameters which aren't required but would aid in refining the results of the annotation. Specifically the function ```scmapCell2Cluster``` function (found [here](https://github.com/ebi-gene-expression-group/scmap-cli/blob/develop/scmap-scmap-cell.R#L103)) in the scmap-cli tool can take two additional parameters:\n- ```w``` an integer specifying the number of nearest neighbours to find\n- ```threshold``` the threshold which the maximum similarity between the query and a reference cell must exceed for the cell-type to be assigned\n\nThese parameters can be found in the documentation [here](https://rdrr.io/bioc/scmap/man/scmapCell2Cluster.html)\n\n---\n\nFor context I am running these tools in a Galaxy workflow on the usegalaxy.eu server.\n\u003cbr\u003e","files":null}]}